archivesspace-development.title: clean up extent pattern "digital folders: [n], digital files: [n]"
move portion/partial info in extent to @altrender

comments.body:
Upon closer consideration, the portion property of the ASpace container appears to be different from our partiality notation.

"2 boxes (1 partial)" is parsed by the importer as 
number --> 2
portion --> [whole by default]
type --> boxes (1 partial)

I.e. it understands a container type "boxes (1 partial)".

The portion property in ASpace appears to indicate the portion of the resource in the container, not the portion of the container occupied by the resource. 

As far as I can see, this means we can't map our partiality references to ASpace, and we can't keep them in the value of extent, either.

figgy.title: Item with multiple holdings/locations not showing up as available for CDL
Fix CDL Eligibility for items with multiple holdings/locations
Rename "master" branch to "main"

comments.body:
Notes:

Esmé's script starts off by deleting the repo locally, then cloning it anew. I wasn't really wanting to do this, for fear of losing local work that I'd stashed or accidentally losing a branch I had wip on. So I ran it in a different location.

Steps:

- Clone Esmé's script to some location, cd there, make it executable
- Run the script
- Change the base/target of all open PRs. They won't close automatically but merging them will merge them to master, not to main.
- Transfer branch protection policies
- All devs will need to update local settings
  - Delete 'master' branch from local clones
  - run `git symbolic-ref --short refs/heads/master refs/heads/main` to protect yourself when you accidentally try to checkout master (this will give you main instead)
  - Not sure what others will encounter, but as a user of the `hub` command line tool I had to run this to ensure my PRs will issue to the correct target base: `git symbolic-ref refs/remotes/origin/HEAD refs/remotes/origin/main`
  - do `git branch -r --delete origin/master` to remove the local reference to `remotes/origin/master`
Note this hasn't been run on figgy yet

pulfalight.title: keep search functionality for name (EAC-CPF) records

comments.body: I will need to review this further, my suspicion is that this is going to require a nested Solr Document for modeling individual `name` entities. An alternative strategy might be to implement an ActiveRecord model and provide some Solr-compliant mapping strategy for the model attributes, but this is slightly more labor intensive.
I've attempted this before with https://github.com/pulibrary/pulfalight/pull/257, and the approach wasn't too terrible to implement.
This will require wireframing for an early attempt to implement the Show View.

It is desired in order to ensure that name authorities will be retrieved with keyword searches, however disambiguation is going to be needed for the search result layout design: https://xd.adobe.com/view/a54bb217-10ff-43b2-72f6-6c3cadf376a4-d37a/screen/3a6835a5-8d84-4e46-9425-143716210f0e
The enhanced UI updates for the search results view might not all be possible to implement for the initial MVP release, and this could be scoped for a later minor release.
